==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Witling
<hw>Wit"ling</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[<ets>Wit</ets> +
<ets>-ling</ets>; cf. G. <ets>witzling</ets>.]</ety> <def>A person who
has little wit or understanding; a pretender to wit or
smartness.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>A beau and <qex>witing</qex> perished in the forming.</q>
<rj><qau>Pope.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Ye newspaper <qex>witlings</qex>! ye pert scribbling folks!</q>
<rj><qau>Goldsmith.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Witness</ent>⟦br⟧
